Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant D'Asia Tate-Guyton appeared by video.  Attorney Sylvan Jaspen appeared by video for D'Asia Tate-Guyton.  Prosecuting attorney Gregg Herman appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm 

Pretrial Conference held.  Defense advises she has not received discovery or offer and requests adjourned status date.  Court grants request.
Status conference scheduled for November 30, 2022 at 09:00 am.
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms. Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant D'Asia Tate-Guyton in court.  Prosecuting attorney M Samir Siddique in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br.30 for a Pretrial Conference.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 31, 2022 at 08:30 am.

ADDRESS INFO for D'Asia Tate-Guyton
Current: 5734 West Villard Avenue, Milwaukee, WI 53209   (Effective: 03-11-2022)
Prior: 5034 West Villard Avenue, Milwaukee, WI 53209
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant D'Asia Tate-Guyton not in court.  Alexandria S. Carlson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. The forfeiture order is stayed for 30 days pending notice to the defendant. Court makes a finding that there is no possible victim identified, therefore, restitution is not an issue.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 3/29/22 @ 2p
